  "title": "Oracle Q4 2024 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2024-12-09T22:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2024_Q4",
  "location": "Austin, TX",
  "url": "https://investor.oracle.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "safra-catz",
      "speaker_name": "Safra Catz",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q2 of fiscal 2025 was excellent. Total revenues were $14.1 billion, up 9% in constant currency. Cloud services and license support revenue was $11.0 billion, up 12%. OCI revenue grew 52% year-over-year. Remaining performance obligations set another record at $97 billion. We are highly confident in delivering cloud revenue of over $25 billion in fiscal 2025 and over $48 billion by fiscal 2029, a goal announced with our board."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "larry-ellison",
      "speaker_name": "Larry Ellison",
      "speaker_role": "CTO & Chairman",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "The generative AI wave is driving an unprecedented data center buildout. Oracle has contracted with multiple nation-state governments to build sovereign AI infrastructure on OCI. We have won AI contracts worth more than $9 billion in the first half of fiscal 2025 alone. OCI's architectural advantages for large-scale AI training — particularly our cluster networking at 3.2 terabits per second — are real and are winning deals."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Brent Thill at Jefferies."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-brent-thill",
      "speaker_name": "Brent Thill",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Safra, can you give us a sense of when the massive backlog starts to convert to revenue at a faster pace, and what's the capital intensity required to serve that backlog?"
    }
  ],
